That is why me personally am against an open recruiting of new guild members.  Especially people you don't know.  I have always been one to hang out with people I know and enjoy grouping with instead of focusing on the tag above their head.  <br>
<br>
Organization and communication are really the only true benefits I think of being in a single guild.  Besides communication issues when you truly think about it having the same tag is of no real advantage.  <br>
<br>
For people who are new to the game being in a guild can help them get a good headstart.  It has always been human nature to help out people who are your family.  In this case the guild being the family.  But as many families are when someone does something wrong to you it leaves a sour taste in your mouth.  You still feel compelled to help them in time of need but, still feel that hesitation in going out of your way to do too much.  Which leads to resentment and eventually dislike and hard feelings.  But in whole all actions of a single player erode or strengthen the whole guild just as much as the actions of all players combined and no matter how hard you try to avoid it some people will inevitably get along better with different members in a guild.  Hence the formation of cliques.  I remember when Raging Fist was around and many people were griping about this very thing.  But, because of playing times, level, and many other reasons this is going to happen.  I was one of the people bitching about it too don't get me wrong, but it is just something that has to happen.  Our guild right now has just enough active members to form 1 group and we hardly ever do stuff together because of some of these things listed above. <br>
<br>
I still enjoy the game, but mainly cause of the people I know and keep getting to know that still play.  If a lot of the people I know and respect left EQ and went to another game like Asheron's call for instance I would go there and never play EQ again.  <br>
<br>
Like Krenna mentioned in a few posts on FW site and our site the burden of leadership in a guild shouldn't have to be a burden.  I know when I was an officer in Raging Fist it was a pain too.  Being a leader and all can be fun and should be fun, after all it is just a game.  Everyone seems to agree with that but sometimes forget it when they get mad and start bashing people and all that other nonsense that goes on sometimes in the game.  I know I have done it.<br>
<br>
So many people wonder what happened to the Raging Fist and why did it die and to put it simply the downfall of it started when mass open recruiting began.  Sometimes I would log on and say &quot;Hail mighty Fist&quot;  and get a lot of responses from people I had never heard of before.  A lot of them were good people, but there were a few real assholes that helped ruin the guild in the long run.  I know near the end of the guild I would read the board and see way too much bashing and envy, etc.. and be disgusted.  But simply put everyone has their idea of leadership and the way things should be run and when things aren't going that way it can cause some dissention and corruption in the guild.  It happens moreso in a very large guild more than in a smaller tidy guild I think.  <br>
<br>
I'm done rambling now and I hope you guys have found a good home for yourselves now.  If I feel the urge to pull out Xeus you will prob see me hanging around since most of the people I used to group with when I still played him you have listed above.     <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub21.ezboard.com/fashesofragefrm1.showMessage?topicID=255.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub21.ezboard.com/fashesofragefrm1.showMessage?topicID=253.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/fashesofragefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=252.topic&index=17><img src=http://www.mindspring.com/~shuman88/Images/reply1.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/fashesofragefrm1.threadControl?topicID=252.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/fashesofragefrm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=252.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub21.ezboard.com/fashesofragefrm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=252.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub21.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="ashesofragefrm1">General<option value="ashesofragefrm2">Members House<option value="ashesofragefrm3">Council Room<option value="ashesofragefrm4">New Members<option value="ashesofragefrm5">Shu's Corner</select></td><td><input type=submit value="Go" class=inputb